gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 117, Spurs 110
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Spurs, 117-110. Karl-Anthony Towns recorded 29 points, 12 rebounds, and two assists for the Timberwolves, while Anthony Edwards added 28 points, seven rebounds, and five assists in the victory. Victor Wembanyama tallied 29 points, nine rebounds, and four assists for the Spurs in the losing effort. The Timberwolves improve to 1-0 in West Group C play, and 6-2 in the regular season, while the Spurs fall to 0-1 in West Group C play, and 3-6 in the regular season.
